This paper is primarily focused on image super-resolution using deep convolutional neural networks, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also introduces a Bayesian approach for uncertainty estimation, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of Monte Carlo sampling and batch normalization layers also suggests a potential connection to neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the practical applications of uncertainty estimation in super-resolution, which could be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
